Then how am I supposed to answer?

00:49:08.240 --> 00:49:12.120
Hurry! What if it’s something important?

00:49:12.960 --> 00:49:14.240
(P’Sea)

00:49:21.640 --> 00:49:22.680
Saint!

00:49:22.680 --> 00:49:25.160
Hello, Sea.

00:49:25.160 --> 00:49:27.160
(Hello, Ice.)

00:49:28.160 --> 00:49:31.040
Hi, what’s up?

00:49:33.040 --> 00:49:34.120
Saint, you bastard!

00:49:34.120 --> 00:49:36.040
You idiot! Damn it!

00:49:36.680 --> 00:49:38.360
Hello, Sea.

00:49:38.360 --> 00:49:39.120
Tomorrow at 3 PM

00:49:39.120 --> 00:49:40.960
come record the test casting for Sin’s role, okay?

00:49:40.960 --> 00:49:43.120
I already announced auditions for Kit’s role.

00:49:43.120 --> 00:49:44.720
A lot of people are interested.

00:49:44.720 --> 00:49:46.000
I’ve selected the ones I think

00:49:46.000 --> 00:49:47.360
would match with you.

00:49:48.520 --> 00:49:50.520
Got it.

00:49:55.600 --> 00:49:59.840
Hey, Saint, come back and untie me first!

00:49:59.840 --> 00:50:01.120
Alright everyone, ready?

00:50:01.120 --> 00:50:02.280
I’ll be giving you a scene

00:50:02.280 --> 00:50:04.360
that’s a little different from the actual script.

00:50:04.360 --> 00:50:06.640
Look at scene eight.

00:50:06.640 --> 00:50:09.160
Sin, whose eyesight is failing

00:50:09.160 --> 00:50:11.360
tries to grab something to wipe his tears.

00:50:11.360 --> 00:50:13.440
He ends up picking up Kit’s shirt.

00:50:13.440 --> 00:50:15.600
Sin accidentally smells it without realizing

00:50:15.600 --> 00:50:17.760
just as Kit walks in and sees it.

00:50:17.760 --> 00:50:18.360
Any questions?

